						               													<description>Climate change has major consequences for all of us. The polar ice caps are also melting.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Volle Scholle, you have to pull your penguins across the melting ice to the finish line as quickly as possible. But watch out! If you risk too much, you'll swim.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player receives two game pieces (penguins). A player may roll the dice as many times as he wants. The numbers 3 to 6 each bring one movement point - if a player stops, he may distribute the movement points earned among his two penguins. On a 1 or 2, all points are lost and it is the next player's turn. After each round the ice melts, penguins standing on melted ice fall into the water and are out of the game. The winner is the player who gets the most penguins to the finish line, in case of a tie the fastest penguin.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The special thing about it: the game consists of only one postcard and can be sent. All other materials needed can be found in a well sorted household. :)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
